## 3.  How to compile & link

```bash
# 1. Compile the C++ stub (requires the real BlockSci headers/libs)
g++ -c -std=c++17 -I$(ocamlc -where) -I/path/to/blocksci/include \
    -fPIC blocksc_stubs.c -o blocksc_stubs.o

# 2. Build a static/dynamic library (optional)
ar rcs libblocksc.a blocksc_stubs.o   # static
# or
g++ -shared -o libblocksc.so blocksc_stubs.o -L/path/to/blocksci/lib -lblocksci

# 3. Compile the OCaml interface
ocamlc -c blocksc.mli

# 4. Link everything together
ocamlopt -o my_program unix.cmxa threads.cmxa blocksc.cmx \
    -cclib -lblocksc -cclib -lblocksci
```

Replace `/path/to/blocksci/...` with the actual include and library directories of your BlockSci installation.

